.TH "ieee80211_calculate_rx_timestamp" 9 "ieee80211_calculate_rx_timestamp" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ieee80211_calculate_rx_timestamp \- calculate timestamp in frame
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u64" ieee80211_calculate_rx_timestamp
.BI "(struct ieee80211_local *local "  ","
.BI "struct ieee80211_rx_status *status "  ","
.BI "unsigned int mpdu_len "  ","
.BI "unsigned int mpdu_offset "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "local" 12
mac80211 hw info struct
.IP "status" 12
RX status
.IP "mpdu_len" 12
total MPDU length (including FCS)
.IP "mpdu_offset" 12
offset into MPDU to calculate timestamp at
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function calculates the RX timestamp at the given MPDU offset, taking
into account what the RX timestamp was. An offset of 0 will just normalize
the timestamp to TSF at beginning of MPDU reception.
